Use Household API Setup to retrieve household details and related records, such as Financial Accounts, Financial Holdings, Assets and Liabilities, and Members with Connect API calls. You donâ€™t have to be a Salesforce developer.

Required editions: Lightning Experience, Professional, Enterprise, and Unlimited Editions.

To aggregate household records, install the household API for the Wealth Management unmanaged package. The package contains the household API Retrieval Summary Definition that retrieves household details.

Confirm that plans and goals feature are enabled in your Salesforce org if you want to use the Household Account record pages.

Record rollup definitions and household API make it easy to view details from two unrelated objects by using record aggregation.

Apply filters to aggregate only the records that matter to users.

Enable Data Pipeline and assign permissions to work with the data processing engine.

Assign Record Aggregation Access permission to users. Install and deploy the Household API for Wealth Management Unmanaged Package.

Create a Household API using customized rollup definitions.
title: Aggregate Records with Salesforce Financial Services Cloud
